						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't suppose you have one of these ICs (or both) and would be willing to produce a pinout?<br /><br />IMO, this would be an easy thing to make using some pin header or a castellated PCB and a handful of 74xx parts.</div><br /><br />I did provide the link, but my post may not have been sufficiently clear.  This is the pinout of the 32-pin BU3270 : <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/nes_pio_pinout.txt">http://nesdev.com/nes_pio_pinout.txt</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I assume the BU3266 is the same, but I can't be sure and my AV Famicom (HVCN-CPU-02) has the BU3270.<br /><br />The BU3266 can be found in the Australian PAL Top Loaders :<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xTRyxJvXbAg">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xTRyxJvXbAg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />In the rare revised NES Top Loader RF version :<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PM-PqovO2zA">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PM-PqovO2zA</a><!-- m --><br /><br />And in the HVCN-CPU-01 AV Famicoms :<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://offgao.blog112.fc2.com/blog-entry-38.html">http://offgao.blog112.fc2.com/blog-entry-38.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />The BU3270 can be found in the rare revised NES Top Loader AV version :<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mEhNt5q7Hl0">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mEhNt5q7Hl0</a><!-- m --></div>

					
