					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Famicoms use H, HC for the '368 and typically use LS (but occasionally HC) for '139.  A pure restoration should use the '368 as an amp, even if it would be less than ideal from a noise perspective.<br /><br />I like your design, it can be extended easily in 3 of 4 directions to add passives like decoupling caps and the negative feedback resistor.  I would not like to add any unnecessary space on the right side of the pins, that could conflict with the NESRGB mod.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nerdlypleasures.blogspot.com/" class="postlink">Nerdly Pleasures - My Vintage Video Game &amp; Computing Blog</a></div>
