			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have not forgotten about this mod, but I believe I was not quite right with the components I need.  I want all five D-inputs for $4016 and $4017.  When you add in /PA13 and SNDIN, you need twelve inverters.  While a 40HC386 has six tri-state inverters, but four are enabled by one pin and two are enabled by another pin.  The inverters for /PA13 and SNDIN always has to be active, however.  This is done on real hardware by using the pair of inverters on one 40HC386 controlled by the secondary enable.  I cannot do that with 40HC386 because the other five inverters must be devoted to the data inputs.  So I have to add a 74HC04 to the board, just like a NES front loader.  In addition, I forgot about the 10K pullups for the input lines, a 10x10K package is needed.  Finally, for the microphone the canonical circuit requires a 10K resistor and a 0.1uF capacitor before the inverter plus another 10K to mix into the audio circuit (optional).  Finally, to eliminate noise, each of the four ICs should have its own decoupling capacitor.  So in short, the BOM looks like this :<br /><br />2 x 40HC368<br />74LS139<br />74HC04<br />2 x 10K<br />10x10K common terminal<br />5 x 0.1uF<br />2 x 16-pin shrink-DIP header<br />Custom PCB that somebody should design <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nerdlypleasures.blogspot.com/" class="postlink">Nerdly Pleasures - My Vintage Video Game &amp; Computing Blog</a></div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

